    Americans have imperfections like everyone else.  One thing about us as a whole is that sooner or later we put them under the microscope and then try to change.  The first protest against slavery was at a Quaker meeting in Philadelphia in the early 1700's.  It took a long time to abolish it, and we're still dealing with the aftereffects.  Paying our debts of honor to all those who fought at our behest in Southeast Asia, like the Hmongs, is something that also still needs much work.
